2.3 Generated Sample Excel Structure

Case A — JEE / NEET (Simplified Schema)
Columns EXCLUDED:
    • Exam
    • Subject
    • Marks
    • NegativeMarks
Marking scheme auto-applied:
Correct: +4
Incorrect: -1
These are stored in template metadata during upload.

Required Columns
    • UniqueKey
    • ChapterName
    • Difficulty (Easy / Medium / Hard)
    • QuestionType
    • QuestionNo
    • QuestionImageFile
    • SolutionImageFile
    • CorrectAnswer
    • PrimaryTag
    • SecondaryTag

Optional Columns (Included in Sample)
    • Topic
    • TutorialVideoLink
    • SimulationLink
    • AdditionalTag
    • InternalNotes
These appear in Student Portal after test (L0+).

Case B — Other Exam
Full schema:
    • Exam
    • Subject
    • Marks
    • NegativeMarks
    • All metadata fields

2.4 Excel Workbook Structure
Workbook must contain:
Sheet 1: questions
Sheet 2: Exam Summary
Sheet 3: INSTRUCTIONS

Exam Summary Sheet
Displays:
    • Selected Exam
    • Selected Subject
    • Marking Scheme
    • Difficulty definitions
    • ZIP creation instructions

INSTRUCTIONS Sheet
Must include:
    • Column-by-column explanation
    • Allowed values
    • Examples
    • Image naming rules
    • ZIP packaging steps
    • Common error list
This reduces support load.

3️⃣ Upload ZIP Flow
Step 1 — Upload ZIP
Extract:
    • questions.xlsx
    • Question images
    • Solution images
Reject if nested folders exist.

Step 2 — Schema Validation
Row-level validation:
Required fields present
Allowed difficulty values
CorrectAnswer format valid
UniqueKey non-empty
Errors must be:
    • Row-specific
    • Human-readable
    • Downloadable CSV
No partial commit.

Step 3 — Image Validation
For each row:
    • QuestionImageFile exists
    • SolutionImageFile exists
    • File names match Excel
No external URLs allowed.

Step 4 — Duplicate Handling
Check:
    • Duplicate UniqueKey in upload
    • Existing UniqueKey in database
Rules:
If question never used → allow overwrite
If question used in assigned run → block structural overwrite

Step 5 — Distribution Preview
Before import, show:
    • Easy / Medium / Hard %
    • Chapter balance
    • Marks balance
    • Missing difficulty warnings
    • Extreme imbalance warning

Step 6 — Confirm Import
Atomic commit:
institutes/{id}/questions/{questionId}
Images stored:
CloudStorage/{instituteId}/questionBank/{questionId}/

